 small enough to satisfy current constraints on\nthe tensor-to-scalar index. Hence, the model either predicts a spectral tilt\nthat is too red, or it overproduces gravitational waves, or both.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 May 2013 20:00:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Aug 2013 19:43:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
