 depend on a rare event,\nsuch as a direct accretion of a satellite galaxy onto the disk of the parent\ngalaxy. While lopsidedness may be caused by several phenomena, moderate\nlopsidedness (<A_1>_i + <A_1>_o)/2 < 0.3) is likely to reflect halo asymmetries\nto which the disk responds or a gravitationally self-generated mode . We\nhypothesize that the magnitude of the stellar response depends both on how\ncentrally concentrated the stars are with respect to the dark matter and\nwhether there are enough stars in the region of the lopsidedness that\nself-gravity is dynamically important.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 May 2013 20:08:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 May 2013 16:35:14 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 28 May 2013 18:24:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
