systems. In place of automata theory, we use only abstract machines and\nmemoization. As case studies, we show the technique applies to a language with\nclosures, garbage collection, stack-inspection, and first-class composable\ncontinuations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 May 2013 14:19:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 May 2013 12:36:14 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 29 Sep 2013 18:10:34 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2013 18:47:21 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 27 Mar 2014 22:39:04 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 10 Jun 2014 16:10:10 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Wed, 6 Aug 2014 14:45:24 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Thu, 14 Aug 2014 21:13:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-08-18"}
